# Worktree Workflow

## Branches

| Branch | Purpose | Direct push |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| `{{git.releaseBranchLabel}}` | Release snapshot when a release branch is configured. | Never |
| `{{git.integrationBranch}}` | Integration branch. Feature PRs target this branch. | Never |
| `feature/{{project.taskPrefix}}-<taskId>-...` | Task branch. | Allowed with `--force-with-lease` |
| `bugfix/...`, `hotfix/...`, `infra/...` | Same role as feature branches. | Allowed with `--force-with-lease` |
| `worktree/<dirname>` | Parking branch for idle worktrees when parking is enabled. | Never |

Do not work directly on protected delivery branches. {{git.protectedBranchRule}} Use a task branch and PR.

## Worktrees

Worktree parking mode: `{{git.worktreeParkingMode}}`.

When parking is enabled, idle worktrees move to local `worktree/<dirname>` branches that track `{{git.integrationRef}}`.

| Worktree | Path | Parking |
|----------|------|---------|
| Main | `<main worktree>` | `{{git.integrationBranch}}` |
| Additional | `<additional worktree>` | `worktree/<dirname>` |

When parking is disabled, skip the parking helper and still run `{{git.deliveryStateCommand}}` so the final report records `{{git.worktreeHygieneSuccessLine}}`.

## Delivery Meaning

These are separate facts. Do not merge them together in close-out wording:

| State | Meaning | Source of truth |
|-------|---------|-----------------|
| `delivered to {{git.integrationBranch}}` | Task branch was merged through PR into `{{git.integrationRef}}`. | Merged feature PR and commit reachability from `{{git.integrationRef}}` |
| `released to {{git.releaseBranchLabel}}` | Integration changes were shipped through the configured release flow. | Merged release PR and release-state evidence |
| `local cleanup` | Current worktree cleanup/parking state. | `git branch -vv`, upstream, HEAD, and `git status` evidence when parking is enabled |

Rules:

- Default `DELIVERY` closes the task into `{{git.integrationBranch}}`, not into `{{git.releaseBranchLabel}}`.
- {{git.releaseSyncAvailability}}
- Local worktree cleanup proves only local hygiene. It does not prove remote delivery or release status.
- Final reports always separate integration status, release status, and local cleanup status.

## Start A Task

```bash
git fetch {{git.remoteName}}
git checkout -b feature/{{project.taskPrefix}}-<taskId>-short-desc {{git.integrationRef}}
```

## Feature Delivery

```bash
gh pr create {{git.prBaseFlag}} --title "feat(scope): ..." --body "..."
gh pr merge <N> --squash
```

Delivery does not stop at PR creation by default. The agent must complete the flow: squash merge, delete the remote branch, run configured cleanup, and record delivery-state evidence. A PR-only stop is valid only when the user explicitly asks for it.

Feature delivery completes the task in `{{git.integrationBranch}}`. By itself, it does not mean the change was released to `{{git.releaseBranchLabel}}`.

## Cleanup After Merge

```bash
{{git.remoteBranchDeleteCommand}}
{{git.worktreeParkCommand}}
{{git.deliveryStateCommand}} --ref {{git.integrationRef}}
```

Postcondition: {{git.worktreePostcondition}}.

Cleanup after merge is local hygiene. It does not change release truth for `{{git.releaseBranchLabel}}`.

## Release Sync

Release sync is separate from default task delivery.

Use it only when the project intentionally ships the accumulated integration branch to the configured release branch. If no release branch is configured, release sync is unavailable.

```bash
gh pr create --base {{git.releaseBranch}} --head {{git.integrationBranch}} --title "release: <milestone>" --body "..."
gh pr merge <N> --squash

git fetch {{git.remoteName}}
git -C <main worktree> reset --hard {{git.releaseRef}}
git -C <main worktree> push --force-with-lease {{git.remoteName}} {{git.integrationBranch}}
```

After a successful release sync, `git diff {{git.releaseRef}} {{git.integrationRef}}` must be empty. SHA equality is not required when branch protection blocks an integration-branch reset; content equality is the invariant.

## Close-out Wording

Every delivery close-out must explicitly report:

- `{{git.integrationBranch}}:` merged / not merged, PR number, commit
- {{git.releaseCloseoutLine}}
- `Local worktree:` parked / skipped / failed, current branch, upstream, `HEAD == {{git.integrationRef}}` yes/no when applicable

Canonical report command:

```bash
{{git.deliveryStateCommand}} --ref <merge-commit-or-{{git.integrationRef}}>
```

## Parallel Worktrees

Before opening a PR, rebase on integration:

```bash
git fetch {{git.remoteName}}
git rebase {{git.integrationRef}}
git push --force-with-lease
```

| Situation | Parallel? |
|-----------|-----------|
| Tasks touch different files | Yes, GitHub can merge them independently. |
| Task B extends files changed by task A | Rebase is required. |
| Task B depends on task A being complete | Run sequentially. |

Rebase conflicts mean the work was dependent and should not continue in parallel without resolving the dependency.
